7 sliced white break cubed and microwaved to dry out -- process crotons in processor until very fine with salt and pepper
2 eggs
1 tbsp of veg oil

mix the eggs and oil

1 tender loin of pork

on bias, cut the loin on bias in 4 slices. On parchment paper, pound loin to 1/4 inch. Season with salt and pepper.

pork -> flour. (shake off) -> egg -> bread crumbs.

once breaded, let dry for 5 minutes.

in lots of veg oil at 375, add meat and shake/shuffle the pot from side to side the entire time. Flip them over and put them on a cooling rack.

garnish with capers, parsly, crumbled egg yoke, a squeeze of lemon.
